inwarde towarde the hele / and the scyatyke vnder the ancle outwarde / and the popletyke that is vnder the kne / and the arenal that is betwene the lytell too and his nexte felowe. ¶Demaunde. Wherof bredeth the synewes that cōmeth to the great leg / and where passe they? Answere. They brede of the laste spondyles of the kydneys / of the holy bone, and the moste parte of them pas by the hole of the thyghe bone / and make muscles in the bought of the 
