nat be made. The thyrde is called the seame conseruatyfe / and it is done as the other be / but it is nat so narowe / for it is nat made but for to mayntayne the lyppes tyll the wounde be closed. ¶Demaunde. In howe many maners is ye incarnatyfe seame made? Answere. In .v. maners. The fyrste is makynge the fyrste stytche in the myddle of the woūde / and the other in meane space of eche syde
