                     de. Is it of necessyte that after it is closed to open it agayne, yf it be lefull to open it in ye same place? Answere. Yes, or in another membre nere to it, or to the next place, as Arnolde of newe towne sayth in his parabolles. ¶Demaunde. Yf they that be canterised with potenciall canteres may be ordred as they be canterysed wt actualles? Answere. Yes saufe that they shal nat be bounde. And also those that blyster make no scarre, whiche must be well applyed, correct, and reprymate of theyr malyces. And after that the blysters be reysed perce theym with cysours or a nedle, and lay a coleworte leafe theron / and couer it with lynnen, and ordre it as ye lyst. And bycause that they be nat blystred nor make no scar thus they fall within .vij. dayes.
               
